cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.AR 

The paper deals with array codes used in storage systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the decoding algorithm, which involves computational complexity and optimization, making it relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.DC). The proposed MDS array code is also applicable to other Vandermonde array codes, making it relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
